                    <msContents>
                        <summary>Kitāb al-Ibānah (Book of Declaration) by ʿUbayd Allāh ibn Muḥammad
                            Ibn Baṭṭah.</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="manuscript_14332_item_1">
                            <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="">Kitāb al-Ibānah ʿan sharīʿat
                                al-firqah al-nājiyah wa-mujānabat al-firaq al-madhmūmah</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ar" type="alt">كتاب الابانة عن شريعة الفرقة الناجية
                                ومجانبة الفرق المذمومة</title>
                            <title xml:lang="en">Book of Declaration of the law of the sect of
                                salvation and aviodance of the blamable sects</title>

                            <author key="person_90049315"><persName xml:lang="en">Ibn Baṭṭah, ʻUbayd
                                    Allāh ibn Muḥammad, 917-997</persName><persName xml:lang="ar"
                                    >ابو عبد الله عبيد الله بن محمد بن محمد بن حمدان بن
                                    بطة</persName></author>
                            <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                            <note><p>A work of traditions concerning Abu Bakr, ʿUthmān and ʿAli, and
                                    the lawfulness of their caliphate, including that of ʿUmar.</p>
                                <p>The book contains only Sections 27 and 28 of the work which must
                                    have been voluminous. Each juzʾ has the full title, the name of
                                    the author and the name of the two Rāwis who vouch for the
                                    authenticity of his text: <persName xml:lang="ar" key="">ابو
                                        القسم علي بن احمد بن محمد بن علي بن البسري</persName>, who
                                    died around 495 AH (1101 CE), and <persName xml:lang="ar" key=""
                                        >الشيخ الامام ابو الحسن علي بن عبيد الله بن نصر بن عبيد الله
                                        بن الزاغوني</persName>, who in 527 AH (1134 CE).</p>
                                <p>The manuscript may be considered as part of one of the copies
                                    made by Ibnuz-Zāghūni's disciples from his own original.</p>
                                <p>The manuscript was transcribed around 510 AH (1116 CE), that is,
                                    before the year 514 AH (1120 CE) in which a note was written at
                                    the end of each part.</p></note>
                            <msItem xml:id="manuscript_14332_item_1-item_1">
                                <locus from="1a" to="24b">1a-24b</locus>
                                <title>Juzʾ 27</title>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="1b" to="8b">1b-8b</locus>
                                    <title>Chapter 1</title>
                                    <note><p><quote>باب خلافة عثمان بن عفان امير المومنين
                                            </quote></p></note>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="8b" to="18a">8b-18a</locus>
                                    <title>Chapter 2</title>
                                    <note><p><quote>باب ذكر خلافة امير المؤمنين علي بن ابي
                                                طالب</quote></p></note>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="18a" to="24b">18a-24b</locus>
                                    <title>Chapter 3</title>
                                    <note><p><quote>باب ذكر اتباع علي بن ابي طالب في ايام حلافته سنن
                                                ابي بكر وعمر وعثمان</quote></p>
                                        <p><locus from="22a">Folio 22a</locus>: mention of the
                                            charter of the Caliphs ʿUmar and ʿAli in favour of the
                                            Dhimmis.</p></note>
                                </msItem>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="manuscript_14332_item_1-item_2">
                                <locus from="25a" to="48b">25a-48b</locus>
                                <title>Juzʾ 28</title>
                                <note><p>This juzʾ contains 23 chapters (bābs).</p></note>
                            </msItem>
                        </msItem>
